king.<br /><br />Same goes for fantasy.  No Tolkien, no list.<br /><br />Pffft!!!!","siteroot":"http://www.livejournal.com","poster":"grrm","stime":"6 years ago","ctime":"April 21 2011, 19:22:33 UTC","massactions":0,"subject":"That list is terrible!","deleted":0,"username":[{"journal_url":"http://hockey-99999.livejournal.com/","striked":null,"journaltype":"P","userhead_url":"http://l-stat.livejournal.net/img/userinfo_v8.svg?v=17080?v=146.10","color":null,"noctxpopup":0,"side_alias":0,"journal":"hockey_99999","inline_css":0,"attrs":null,"is_identity":0,"bold":1,"show_userhead":1,"username":"hockey_99999","user_alias":"","profile_url":"http://hockey-99999.livejournal.com/profile","alias":0}],"dname":"hockey_99999","ctime_ts":1303413753,"tracked":0},{"shown":1,"collapsed":0,"userpic":"http://l-userpic.livejournal.com/91237832/7059164","actions":[{"allowed":1,"href":"http://grrm.livejournal.com/212009.html?thread=13145129#t13145129","name":"permalink","title":"link"},{"allowed":1,"href":"http://grrm.livejournal.com/212009.html?thread=13145129#t13145129","name":"collapse","title":"Collapse"},{"allowed":1,"href":"http://grrm.livejournal.com/212009.html?thread=13145129#t13145129","name":"expand","title":"Expand"}],"uname":"grrm","loaded":1,"p_tracked":0,"commenter_journal_base":"http://grrm.livejournal.com/","statprefix":"http://l-stat.livejournal.net","dtalkid":13145129,"talkid":51348,"thread_url":"http://grrm.livejournal.com/212009.html?thread=13145129#t13145129","above":13144873,"upictitle":"George R.R. Martin: Spain","article":"Uh...Tolkien was published by Allen & Unwin.  <br /><br />The world, and the UK, has more than one publisher.<br /><br />","siteroot":"http://www.livejournal.com","poster":"grrm","stime":"6 years ago","below":13154345,"ctime":"April 21 2011, 19:55:24 UTC","parent":13144873,"massactions":0,"subject":"Re: That list is terrible!","deleted":0,"username":[{"journal_url":"http://grrm.livejournal.com/","striked":null,"journaltype":"P","userhead_url":"http://l-stat.livejournal.net/img/userinfo_v8.svg?v=17080?v=146.10","color":null,"noctxpopup":0,"side_alias":0,"journal":"grrm","inline_css":0,"attrs":null,"is_identity":0,"bold":1,"show_userhead":1,"username":"grrm","user_alias":"","profile_url":"http://grrm.livejournal.com/profile","alias":0}],"dname":"grrm","ctime_ts":1303415724,"tracked":0},{"shown":1,"collapsed":0,"userpic":"http://l-userpic.livejournal.com/49489555/203620","actions":[{"allowed":1,"href":"http://grrm.livejournal.com/212009.html?thread=13154345#t13154345","name":"permalink","title":"link"},{"allowed":1,"href":"http://grrm.livejournal.com/212009.html?thread=13154345#t13154345","name":"collapse","title":"Collapse"},{"allowed":1,"href":"http://grrm.livejournal.com/212009.html?thread=13154345#t13154345","name":"expand","title":"Expand"}],"uname":"ruthanolis","loaded":1,"p_tracked":0,"commenter_journal_base":"http://ruthanolis.livejournal.com/","statprefix":"http://l-stat.livejournal.net","dtalkid":13154345,"talkid":51384,"thread_url":"http://grrm.livejournal.com/212009.html?thread=13154345#t13154345","above":13145129,"upictitle":"Ruthless: emblem","article":"I had more than enough trouble picking one of each from what was on offer.  Just because your favourite author isn't included isn't a sin.  Between classic science fiction authors like James Blish, Philip K. Dick, Frank Herbert, Theodore Sturgeon, Arthur C. Clarke, Larry Niven, Poul Anderson and H. G. Wells, and some of the more contemporary ones, how can you be complaining about people missing?<br />The same goes for the list of fantasy authors.  I was impressed they were able to get so many onto it.<br />The 'egregious' omission of some authors is only to be expected.  You can't fit everybody onto the winner's podium.<br /><br />All that aside, I was really happy to be reminded of one of the first sci-fi stories ever suggested to me by my father - Last And First Men by Olaf Stapledon.","siteroot":"http://www.livejournal.com","poster":"grrm","st